    {
      "segments": [
        {
          "scid": "sn12.37:1.1",
          "pli": "Sāvatthiyaṃ viharati. ",
          "en": "At Sāvatthī. "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn12.37:1.2",
          "pli": "“Nāyaṃ, bhikkhave, kāyo tumhākaṃ napi aññesaṃ. ",
          "en": "“Mendicants, this body doesn’t belong to you or to anyone else. "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn12.37:1.3",
          "pli": "Purāṇamidaṃ, bhikkhave, kammaṃ abhisaṅkhataṃ abhisañcetayitaṃ vedaniyaṃ daṭṭhabbaṃ. ",
          "en": "It’s old deeds, and should be seen as produced by choices and intentions, as something to be felt. "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn12.37:2.1",
          "pli": "Tatra kho, bhikkhave, sutavā ariyasāvako paṭiccasamuppādaññeva sādhukaṃ yoniso manasi karoti: ",
          "en": "A learned noble disciple carefully and properly attends to dependent origination itself: "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn12.37:2.2",
          "pli": "‘iti imasmiṃ sati idaṃ hoti, imassuppādā idaṃ uppajjati; ",
          "en": "‘When this exists, that is; due to the arising of this, that arises. "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn12.37:2.3",
          "pli": "imasmiṃ asati idaṃ na hoti, imassa nirodhā idaṃ nirujjhati, yadidaṃ—",
          "en": "When this doesn’t exist, that is not; due to the cessation of this, that ceases. That is: "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn12.37:2.4",
          "pli": "avijjāpaccayā saṅkhārā; ",
          "en": "Ignorance is a condition for choices. "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn12.37:2.5",
          "pli": "saṅkhārapaccayā viññāṇaṃ … pe … ",
          "en": "Choices are a condition for consciousness. … "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn12.37:2.6",
          "pli": "evametassa kevalassa dukkhakkhandhassa samudayo hoti. ",
          "en": "That is how this entire mass of suffering originates. "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn12.37:2.7",
          "pli": "Avijjāya tveva asesavirāganirodhā saṅkhāranirodho; ",
          "en": "When ignorance fades away and ceases with nothing left over, choices cease. "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn12.37:2.8",
          "pli": "saṅkhāranirodhā viññāṇanirodho … pe … ",
          "en": "When choices cease, consciousness ceases. … "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn12.37:2.9",
          "pli": "evametassa kevalassa dukkhakkhandhassa nirodho hotī’”ti. ",
          "en": "That is how this entire mass of suffering ceases.’” "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn12.37:2.10",
          "pli": "Sattamaṃ. ",
          "en": ""
        }
      ],
